          You have been trained in the ancient traditions of dwarven artisanship. For years you labored under a dwarf master of the craft, enduring long hours and dismissive, sour-tempered treatment in order ot gain the fine skills you possess today. Because you are not a dwarf yourself, you have taken a solemn oath never to take on an apprentice in the craft: it is not for non-dwarves to pass on the skills of Moradin's favored children.
